description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A unique opportunity has arisen for a committed and compassionate nurse with an enthusiasm for delivering high standards of care to join the dynamic and supportive team on the intensive care/high dependency unit at Northern Devon Healthcare Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will enable the successful applicants to develop their knowledge and skills in caring for critically ill adults/children within a supported environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have good assessment skills, work well within a multidisciplinary team, enjoy daily challenges, and are passionate about learning and providing high quality care this position could be for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be shift work, including days, nights, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that full-time and part-time positions are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further Information contact Clinical Matron for Critical Care Juliet Parkin on 01271 370269&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 10/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
